latestIgtvVideos.title: Orcas Island Leather Bag DIY
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I finally finished my @orcasislandleathergoods Striped Islander DIY bag! 🎉🎉

This whole bag took me between 9-10 hours, and I can honestly say each minute of it was enjoyable. 

They have a wide variety of DIY craft leather items like tote bags, wallets, a chess set, catch-all’s, and other purses. 

The Striped Islander Bag is a timeless bag, which is what drew me to it. You can choose either coffee (like mine), teal or red for accent colors. It comes with a magnetic clasp, inside & outside pockets, and the strap is adjustable! 

When you place an order with @orcasislandleathergoods you receive everything you could need! Needles, pre-cut leather, thread. All of their guides are online that allow for easy reference! 

Guys, I can only speak positively about this small family business & their products! We will be doing a giveaway with them coming up - as well as a podcast episode. 

If you want to order yours today, click the link in our bio 🎉 it leads you to our affiliate link that gives us a small kickback for referring you.

latestPosts.caption:
📍 BUCKETLIST WASHINGTON CALENDAR - BY MONTH 📍 For local Washingtons and out-of-state visitors planning a trip, there’s’s something to do each month here 🌲🥾🏔️
.
More easy, everyday PNW adventures @adventuresoncall
.
JANUARY
• Ski or Snowboard: Visit Stevens Pass, Crystal Mountain, White Pass, or Mt. Baker
• Bavarian Icefest in Leavenworth
.
FEBRUARY
• Cozy A frame cabin
• Shuck oysters at a glamping resort
• Snowshoe at Artist Point and Gold Creek
.
MARCH
• Daffodil Bloom in La Conner
• Cherry Blossoms Festival and see blooms in Washington Quad, Washington Arboretum, Japanese Garden
• Winthrop Hot Air Balloon Festival
.
APRIL
• Tulip Festival in Skagit Valley
• Book a whale watching tour
•  Soak in a hot spring - Sol Duc, Carson, Doe Bay, Goldmyer
.
MAY
• Explore historic towns - Gig Harbor, Port Townshend, Coupeville, Roslyn
• Walk the new Waterfront Park at Pike Place and Seattle Aquarium
• Paddleboard/Kayak in a lake
.
JUNE
• Strawberry Picking
• Road trip to Olympic National Park to see rainforests, mountains, and beaches
• Explore Deception Pass and walk the bridge
•  Tidepooling at the beach
.
JULY
• Take a ferry to the San Juan, Bainbridge, or Whidbey Island
• Hiking in Cascade National Park
• Lavender Festival in Sequim
.
AUGUST
• Sunflower Blooms
• Go wild blackberry picking
• Blueberry picking
• Music Concert in the Gorge Amphitheater
.
SEPTEMBER
• Washington State Fair in Puyallup
• Apple picking, cider donuts, and fall festivals in Snohomish
• Fall foliage at Mount Rainier
• Wineries - Woodinville, Walla Walla, Lake Chelan
.
OCTOBER
• Pumpkin Patches and Corn Mazes in Snohomish or Skagit County
• Oktoberfest at a dog friendly brewery
• Golden Larch Hikes in Maple Pass Loop or Enchantments
.
NOVEMBER
• Make s’mores, drink hot cocoa, and enjoy a hot tub in a cabin
• Check out museums - Seattle Art Museum, MoPOP, MOHAI, Museum of Flight
• Chase waterfalls: Snoqualmie Falls, Wallace Falls, Palouse Falls
.
DECEMBER
•  Bavarian Christmas in Leavenworth
•  Seattle Christmas Market
•  Zoolights at Seattle and Tacoma zoos
•  Snowflake Lane

latestPosts.caption:
Washington State, a diverse and fascinating region of the Pacific Northwest, has a lot to offer. The @exploringwashingtonstate podcast is our four time weekly show that highlights and showcases the people, places, and experiences that make our state unique. 

Whether you are a lifelong Washingtonian, a newcomer, or even a tourist, the podcast offers something for everyone. You can expect to hear interviews with locals who are making a difference in their communities, in-depth explorations of the state's history & culture, travel & hiking tips, and so much more. 

If you are ready to get to know our state better, tune in today, it is streaming everywhere! 

In our most recent interviews we sat down with @LouMaxon  to speak about design, music, and playing hockey with Wayne Gretzky. @craig.romano to chat all about hiking, trails in Washington, and learned more about his infamous guidebooks. We even spoke with @JJA66, Scuba Jess to learn more about the underwater world in Washington.

latestPosts.caption:
✈️This is NOT Provence, France. This is not even in Europe.
📍This is Washington (🪻+ 🏔️)
.
👋🏻 More everyday PNW adventures for busy people @adventuresoncall
.
☀️ Did you know that lavender is a huge industry in Washington, even though lavender likes very dry, hot weather?
.
💜The PNW is infamous for rain, but there are unique microclimates (mild winters, low precipitation, abundant sunshine) which is perfect for lavender cultivation. In fact, Sequim is the Lavender Capital of North America
.
🪻Peak Lavender blooming season is now! Blooms are late June through early August
🪻 This year’s Sequim Lavender Festival is July 18 - July 20, 2025 (Personally I prefer other days for less crowds)
🪻 Places to find lavender farms include Sequim, Whidbey Island, Ferndale, Olympia, and Woodinville
🪻Sequim Lavender Trail is a scenic driving / cycling route on a tour of the lavender farms in Sequim open all summer long.
🪻Check for U-pick and dog friendly options (many are dog friendly)! 🐾
🪻 Many lavender farms have stores open all year - highly recommend trying lavender ice cream, lavender lemonade, lavender jam, lavender soaps/lotions, and more 🍦
.
🏔️And you can get lavender + Mt Rainier views on a clear day
.
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
When time folds itself into quiet corners of the city. 

#seattlewashington #seattle #aerialphotography #dronephotography

. “Last night, the sky spoke louder than words.”

Last night, Seattle lit up like never before. From the calm waters of Lake Union to the roar of the crowd at Gas Works Park, every firework felt like a heartbeat—louder, brighter, closer. Watching from above, it didn’t feel real. It felt like a movie scene you didn’t want to end. Moments like these remind us why we stay, why we watch, and why we celebrate under the same sky. If you missed it—this is what the 4th of July looked like in the heart of the city.

.

.

.

Up here, the city doesn’t sleep — it exhales.
Sunbeams kissing glass, rooftops glowing, the sky melting into the Sound…

📍That moment when you’re floating above the 206, and for a split second, nothing else matters.
⁣
This ain’t just a view — it’s a vibe.
⁣
💭 Ever watched the sun set on a city that’s still dreaming big?
This is it. And yes, it’s every bit as unreal as it looks.
